parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates to engage
the vehicle jerks or lurches when shifting gears
the transmission fluid leaks
and the check engine light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering hose can cause a fire, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The power steering hose cracks or leaks
and the vehicle catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light stays on
the airbag warning light comes on intermittently
the airbag deploys unexpectedly
the airbag does not deploy in a crash
the seatbelt buckles but the light stays on
the passenger airbag sensor is faulty
the driver's side airbag sensor is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty Takata airbag inflators can cause the airbag to deploy unexpectedly, or not deploy at all in the event of a crash, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light stays on
the airbag warning light comes on intermittently
the airbag deploys unexpectedly
the airbag does not deploy in a crash
the passenger airbag sensor is faulty
the driver's side airbag sensor is faulty.
